responsibilities: Develop SQL queries / ETL packages using T-SQL and SSIS to ingest data from source systems to integrate with SQL Server data warehouse.

analysis:
The job responsibilities and skills listed focus primarily on data management, data warehousing, ETL processes, and business intelligence (BI) tools. The responsibilities include developing SQL queries, designing data models, creating dashboards and reports, and troubleshooting database issues. The skills required include experience with SQL Server, data visualization tools like Power BI, and familiarity with agile development methodologies.

There is a mention of "Machine Learning services" under the skills section, which could potentially involve some AI-related tasks. However, there is no explicit mention of working with Generative AI (GenAI) or language models (LLMs) such as developing, training, or deploying these models. The focus is more on traditional data processing and BI tasks rather than on AI or language model development.

Overall, the job seems to be centered around data engineering and business intelligence rather than AI or language model development.
